rule (query language)applying|( Apply-rulesThe function apply_rules is the rule analog of find-assertionsfind_assertions (section4.4.4.3). It takes as input a pattern and a frame, and it forms a stream of extension frames by applying rules from the data base. Stream-flatmapThe function stream_flatmap maps apply-a-ruleapply_a_rule down the stream of possibly applicable rules (selected by fetch-rulesfetch_rules, section4.4.4.5) and combines the resulting streams of frames.
